content:
Add Terms and Conditions Acceptance to your Pre-Chat Form.

Available in Lightning Experience. This article applies to Messaging for In-App and Messaging for Web channels.

To set up this feature: Customize Application AND Modify Metadata Through Metadata API Functions.

From Setup, enter Embedded Service Deployments, select View, Edit Settings, and click Show Terms and Conditions in pre-chat and Require users to accept Terms and Conditions before chatting.

Save your changes, then Set Custom Labels by selecting Pre-Chat, Terms and Conditions, Standard, and entering the Terms and Conditions message and URL.

Copy the placeholder created from filling out the fields, paste it into your message, and click Finish.

Republish your deployment from the Embedded Service Settings page.
title: Implementing Terms and Conditions Acceptance in Pre-Chat Forms
